		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Modulo operation</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:252px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Divmod.svg" class="image" title="Quotient (red) and remainder (green) functions using different algorithms."><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/2/22/Divmod.svg/250px-Divmod.svg.png" width="250" height="417" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Divmod.svg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
Quotient (red) and remainder (green) functions using different algorithms.</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>In <a href="/wiki/Computing" title="Computing">computing</a>, the <b>modulo</b> operation finds the <a href="/wiki/Remainder" title="Remainder">remainder</a> of <a href="/wiki/Division_(mathematics)" title="Division (mathematics)">division</a> of one number by another.</p>
<p>Given two numbers, <big><span class="texhtml"><var>a</var></span></big> (the dividend) and <big><span class="texhtml"><var>n</var></span></big> (the divisor), <i>a</i> <b>modulo</b> <i>n</i> (abbreviated as <i>a</i> mod <i>n</i>) is the remainder, on division of <i>a</i> by <i>n</i>. For instance, the expression "7 mod 3" would evaluate to 1, while "9 mod 3" would evaluate to 0. Although typically performed with <i>a</i> and <i>n</i> both being integers, many computing systems allow other types of numeric operands.</p>
<p>See <a href="/wiki/Modular_arithmetic" title="Modular arithmetic">modular arithmetic</a> for an older and related convention applied in <a href="/wiki/Number_theory" title="Number theory">number theory</a>.</p>
